00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:03,380
 That's the manner in which we move.

276
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:06,620
 But notice courage is given from God,

277
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:08,020
 which implies something really important.

278
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:11,500
 It implies that courage is not your factory setting.

279
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:14,020
 Like it's not your default mentality.

280
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:15,860
 Fear is.

281
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:20,320
 Fear is the default setting for people that do not know God.

282
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:22,660
 And we get that because we're all tyrannized

283
00:12:22,660 --> 00:12:23,820
 by some kind of fear.

284
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:26,780
 Fear of the future, fear of failure, fear of man,

285
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:29,100
 fear of the outsider, fear of death,

286
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,140
 fear of not being enough.

287
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:32,900
 Whatever it is, you can name your fear for yourself.

288
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:37,220
 That is your default mode until Jesus.

289
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:38,820
 But then Jesus steps into your story

290
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:40,220
 and he changes everything.

291
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,260
 And as he changes everything,

292
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:45,340
 he moves you from a mentality of fear

293
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:48,140
 and into a mentality of courage,

294
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,860
 which is really important to understand.

295
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:55,820
 Because as he gives you a spirit of courage,

296
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:58,540
 that insinuates something so important.

297
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,060
 And I want you to catch this

298
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:02,020
 'cause I think you're gonna want it.

299
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:04,020
 He gives you a spirit of courage

300
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:07,740
 because he does not intend for you

301
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:11,060
 to live a lame Christianity.

302
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:14,060
 He gives you a spirit of courage

303
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:19,060
 because his future for you is not small nor insignificant.

304
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:21,660
 He gives you a spirit of courage

305
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:26,340
 because he wants a future that is big and it is bold instead.

306
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,820
 That is his intent for your life.

307
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:31,340
 He wants you to have a courage

308
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:33,820
 that moves past low risk environments

309
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:35,980
 and steps into high risk environments

310
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:37,860
 because that's what courage is needed for.

311
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:40,460
 Like no one needs courage to tell their mom, hello.

312
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:43,980
 But fellas, you need courage to tell her hello.

313
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:45,260
 You know, like that's different.

314
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:46,660
 There's a different level of risks there.

315
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,820
 And what we know is that the higher the risk,

316
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:50,380
 the higher the reward.

317
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:53,060
 And so if Jesus is calling you into a life

318
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:57,060
 where courage must be your default setting, your mentality,

319
00:13:57,060 --> 00:13:58,700
 what that insinuates is, yes, okay,

320
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,740
 there's going to be some risk,

321
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:05,100
 but there's also gonna be some reward.

322
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:08,260
 There's going to be something in my journey with him

323
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:10,940
 through this life that is going to be fulfilling,

324
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:12,340
 that's going to be meaningful,

325
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:13,740
 that's going to be worthwhile.

326
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:15,260
 And we all want that.

327
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:16,380
 You want that.

328
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:17,860
 I know you do 'cause I talk to you

329
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:21,220
 every single week down front or out in that coffee shop

330
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:23,660
 that you walk through people that want to leave a legacy

331
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:25,460
 and make a difference and change the world

332
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,460
 and find fulfillment.

333
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:29,060
 That's what young adults want.

334
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:31,860
 And the amazing thing that Paul is telling us

335
00:14:31,860 --> 00:14:36,260
 as God gives you a gift through the spirit of courage

336
00:14:36,260 --> 00:14:41,620
 is he wants that for you more than you want that for yourself.

337
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:44,420
 He's looking at you and he's like,

338
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:46,260
 oh, you want to leave a legacy?

339
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:47,300
 You want to change the world?

340
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:48,340
 You want to find fulfillment?

341
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:51,140
 I want that for you more than you want that for yourself.

342
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:54,300
 And yet here's the issue.

343
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:57,780
 If we're in agreement, God, why then isn't that my reality?

344
00:14:57,780 --> 00:15:02,860
 Because we're not as courageous as we think.

345
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:09,020
 We're not as courageous as we think.

346
00:15:09,020 --> 00:15:13,100
 You see, we set great goals,

347
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:16,540
 but what we fail to realize in view of our great goals

348
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,020
 is that those great goals actually fall short

349
00:15:19,020 --> 00:15:20,380
 of the greatness of God

350
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:23,140
 and the goals he would set for your life instead.

351
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:25,380
 And so what we do is rather than focusing

352
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:29,060
 on changing eternity, we focus on changing the world.

353
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:33,940
 Rather than working to leave behind a spiritual legacy,

354
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:37,700
 we just focus on leaving behind a physical legacy.

355
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:40,620
 When we could be making a difference forever,

356
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:43,460
 instead we just focus on making a difference today.

357
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:45,300
 I'm not saying that those things are not good,

358
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,860
 but I am saying those things are not of God.

359
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:52,860
 God wants your life to be purposed into something

360
00:15:52,860 --> 00:15:56,980
 that transcends the barriers of our time

361
00:15:56,980 --> 00:16:01,100
 and extends into the future forever.

362
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,540
 That's the kind of greatness he's calling you into.

363
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:06,860
 That's the sort of courage he has given you for.

364
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:11,900
 John Shedd says, "A ship in harbor is safe,

365
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,980
 "but that's not what ships are built for."

366
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:18,100
 Some of you hear that and you're like, "Yes, I want that.

367
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:20,460
 "I wanna set out onto the open ocean.

368
00:16:20,460 --> 00:16:22,180
 "I wanna raise my sail.

369
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:23,380
 "I wanna catch the wind.

370
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:25,660
 "I want to voyage into the future."

371
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:29,420
 And yet often what we know is we dream dreams

372
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:31,460
 that often are too small for God

373
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:33,500
 because we fear looking odd or different

374
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:36,340
 or strange or weird in the eyes of the world.

375
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:39,020
 And because we do, hear me,

376
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:42,260
 we settle for the creature comforts

377
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:44,740
 of a casual Christian life

378
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:50,100
 when the radical reward of a courageous life

379
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,940
 is waiting for you instead.

380
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:55,900
 That's why we have to fan the flame.

381
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:57,340
 That's why we have to keep the fire.

382
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:59,900
 That's why we have to cultivate our courage

383
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,940
 because while God has given us the gift,

384
00:17:01,940 --> 00:17:03,980
 it's our job to keep the gift.

385
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:05,900
 So how do we do that?

386
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,420
 How do you keep your fire burning?

387
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:10,180
 Well, I'll put it very simply,

388
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,300
 though there's a lot that we could say,

389
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,740
 I would just simply tell you

390
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:15,820
 what we believe in our family, Brooke and I,

391
00:17:15,820 --> 00:17:19,900
 that you just say yes to whatever God asks.

392
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,100
 That's it.

393
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,340
 You just say yes to whatever God asks.

394
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:26,780
 We have a family motto that we wanna live our lives

395
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:29,060
 on the cutting edge of faith,

396
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:31,300
 which just means we wanna live

397
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,020
 where the fighting is fiercest.

398
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:34,780
 We know we wanna be in a place

399
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:36,980
 where God has to be greatest.

400
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:39,340
 If we're in a place of life

401
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:40,740
 where God is not required to move,

402
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:42,980
 why would we wanna be there?

403
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:45,820
 We wanna be where God has to make himself known

404
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:49,340
 to be exactly who he says he is.

405
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:54,340
 And so we say yes to him as often as possible.

406
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:57,020
 Now, those yeses look different

407
00:17:57,020 --> 00:17:58,940
 over the course of our lives.

408
00:17:58,940 --> 00:18:00,740
 Like they've looked small and they've looked big

409
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:01,740
 and they've looked peculiar

410
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:03,740
 and they've looked uncertain at different times.

411
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:07,060
 I mean, it's looked as small as just going across the street

412
00:18:07,060 --> 00:18:10,180
 and watering the widow neighbor's plants.

413
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:14,980
 It's looked as personal as taking our guest bedroom

414
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:17,260
 and opening it up and inviting a girl

415
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:18,500
 who'd been kicked out from her family

416
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,900
 to live with us for a season

417
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,620
 until she could get her feet back underneath her.

418
00:18:22,620 --> 00:18:26,500
 It looked as unpredictable as leaving community

419
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:29,420
 and stepping away from our city and journeying someplace

420
00:18:29,420 --> 00:18:30,900
 we never thought we would live

421
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:35,500
 because there was no ministry there that needed to be there.

422
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:40,340
 You just say yes to God.

423
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:42,860
 Now, I'm not putting us up here as the example to follow.

424
00:18:42,860 --> 00:18:45,700
 We have said no far too many times

425
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,460
 and every single no we have lived to regret.

426
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:52,540
 And so I'm imploring you don't say no

427
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:56,180
 when God is asking you to say yes.

428
00:18:56,180 --> 00:18:59,540
 So where's he asking you for your yes tonight?

429
00:18:59,540 --> 00:19:02,940
 Like, is it finally to come clean

430
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:06,200
 of the last 2% of your sin struggle

431
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,140
 that you've been hiding away and keeping in the dark

432
00:19:08,140 --> 00:19:09,500
 because you don't know what people will think of you

433
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:12,700
 if you actually come forward about it all?

434
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:14,500
 Is it yes to joining region

435
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,180
 and actually working through your past

436
00:19:17,180 --> 00:19:19,340
 as opposed to ignoring that that thing happened

437
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:20,580
 and as long as I don't look at it,

438
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:21,980
 I don't have to remember it?

439
00:19:21,980 --> 00:19:27,900
 Is it yes to talking to your coworker about Jesus?

440
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,760
 And I don't mean talking to them in a way

441
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:32,060
 where you're trying to intellectually armbar them

442
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:34,620
 into submitting into devotion to Christ.

443
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:37,160
 I'm talking to you about visiting with them in a way

444
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:40,720
 where you just ask them, hey, what do you think of God?

445
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,440
 And then letting the conversation flow naturally

446
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,760
 and visiting with them about the person of Jesus.

447
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:47,180
 Like, is it saying yes to writing a letter

448
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:49,240
 and building a bridge with that estranged sibling,

449
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:51,040
 brother, sister that you haven't spoken to

450
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:54,320
 in weeks, months, even years?

451
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:57,500
 Maybe it's yes to answering Tyler's call

452
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,960
 and filling out an application

453
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,340
 and joining us here at The Porch

454
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:02,400
 and leveraging your life for a cause

455
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,240
 that is bigger than yours.

456
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,160
 I'm not talking about the cause of The Porch,

457
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,320
 I'm talking about the cause of the kingdom.

458
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:09,240
 There is a yes that God is asking of you,

459
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:13,080
 so why wouldn't you say yes to it?

460
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:17,200
 Because listen to me, Noah, he said yes to building an ark

461
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,800
 when the earth had never rained.

462
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:25,120
 And God used his family in the process of recreation.

463
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:27,380
 Abraham said yes to following God

464
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:29,960
 when he didn't even know where God was taking him.

465
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,800
 And it was through Abraham

466
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:37,080
 that he became the father of many nations.

467
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:41,300
 Moses said yes to confronting Pharaoh.

468
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:45,240
 And God, he performed signs and wonders

469
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:49,160
 as he delivered his own people out of Egypt.

470
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,920
 Ruth said yes to Naomi,

471
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:54,400
 and God made her the ancestral mother to the Messiah.

472
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,680
 David said yes to facing Goliath,

473
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,720
 and God made him king over his people.

474
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:02,280
 Elijah said yes to confronting the prophets of Baal,

475
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,360
 and God sent fire from heaven.

476
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:07,440
 And best of all, Jesus said yes to the cross

477
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,800
 when no man in his right mind would have.

478
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,200
 And yet because he said yes,

479
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:14,580
 God raised him in victory over sin and death.

480
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:18,520
 Why don't you say yes?

481
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:22,800
 It's through your yes

482
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,680
 that you kindle the flame of your courage.

483
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:28,880
 You cultivate the gift God has given.

484
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:32,120
 You see, you believe big about God.

485
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:34,200
 You believe big about God,

486
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:38,240
 and then you say yes to putting yourself in positions

487
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:41,200
 where he becomes big as a result.

488
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:46,460
 And when you do, that changes everything

489
00:21:46,460 --> 00:21:48,120
 about the way you lead your life.

490
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:53,740
 It leads you to not just move through this world casually,

491
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:56,880
 but it leads you to embrace opportunity,

492
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,780
 even if it is risky,

493
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,920
 which is what Paul goes on to say next.

494
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,720
 He tells us in verse eight,

495
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:06,000
 "Therefore, because God has given you a spirit of courage,

496
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,120
 "do not be ashamed of the testimony about our Lord,

497
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:10,520
 "nor of me, his prisoner, but share in suffering

498
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:13,000
 "for the gospel by the power of God."

499
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:18,000
 So we've already clarified that God has given you a courage

500
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,160
 that's going to lead you into a life that is rewarding,

501
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,800
 but it will require risk.

502
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,720
 And Paul tells you right here,

503
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:26,440
 "Hey, it's gonna require two risks of you very specifically.

504
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:30,920
 "It's not isolated to these two and these two alone,

505
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:33,440
 "but it certainly will be these two and these two alone."

506
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,880
 And I love the two that Paul gives us

507
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,960
 because it shows that Paul, he knows his audience.

508
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,600
 He understands Christians very well

509
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,640
 because he actually points to the two risks

510
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:42,640
 that we're often most gun-shy about

511
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:44,080
 when it comes to our faith.

512
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:46,640
 Telling people about Jesus

513
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:51,400
 and suffering well whenever hardship comes.

514
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,120
 Those are the two things that Paul does.

515
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:54,960
 Why would he do that?

516
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,400
 Why would he say this?

517
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:59,240
 Because Paul knows your second point,

518
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:01,380
 courageous faith is uncensored faith.

519
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:04,200
 Courageous faith is uncensored faith.

520
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:07,160
 Like courageous faith,

521
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,240
 it's unashamed of what other people think

522
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:12,640
 and it is unafraid of any difficulty ahead.

523
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:15,880
 So I was thinking about how to illustrate this to you.

524
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,480
 And I just thought, okay, if you're a sports fan,

525
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:19,600
